    "name": "Lumina — Register USDC/USDT/DAI literal stablecoin feeds in LuminaOracle",
    "description": "DepegShield references stablecoin assets as literal bytes32 strings (\"USDC\", \"USDT\", \"DAI\"). The current LuminaOracle has these feeds registered ONLY under their keccak256 hash, not under the literal bytes32-string. This batch registers the missing literal entries so DepegShield will be able to query the oracle once it is itself registered in CoverRouter. Same Chainlink feed addresses, same staleness (86400s = 24h) as the existing keccak entries — only the asset key changes. Caller MUST be the Timelock (0xd0De5D53dCA2D96cdE7FAf540BA3f3a44fdB747a), which is the owner of LuminaOracle.",
